name: pyroglutamyl-peptidase I
reaction: Release of an N-terminal pyroglutamyl group from a polypeptide, the second amino acid generally not being Pro
comment: A cysteine peptidase, known from bacteria, plants and animals. The enzyme from bacterial sources is used in protein sequencing, and is the type example of peptidase family C15.
